"'''Lumrunners'''" is a short story co-written by [[John Beyer]] and [[Wayne Humfleet]]. It was published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 9|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 9]] by [[West End Games]] in [[February]] [[1996]].

==Plot summary==
On [[Gallisport]], [[Imperial Office of Customs/Legends|Imperial customs]] officer [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Alijah Orr]] receives a tip about the [[PB-950 patrol boat|Corellian PB-950]] ''[[Lumrunner]]'' allegedly attempting to smuggle weapons. Disliking the cockiness of the ship’s owner, Captain [[Shamus Falconi]], Orr decides to personally oversee the inspection. While waiting for the ship to land, Captain of the Port [[Renea Luies]] identifies four individuals in the docking bay, including [[Dutan Lee]] and [[Chop Harlison]], two locals with minimal or no criminal history.

Aboard the ''Lumrunner'', Falconi and his first mate [[Grasheel]], manage to scan the starport and quickly realize an inspection is imminent. They discreetly signal the landing party and instruct them to bluff their way through the check.

Claiming this inspection to be an Imperial matter, Orr dismisses Luies and begins inspecting the cargo. He firstly opens the crates waiting for pickup, finding only mining equipment, surprising even the owner Dutan Lee, who was supposed to be smuggling weapons offplanet. On the ship, Orr and his team start searching the rear of the cargo hold, confident the smugglers would hide any contraband at the back. However, only the expected [[Lum/Legends|lum]] and [[Corellian wine/Legends|wine]] are found. In other crates, the stormtroopers discover industrial repulsor coils, but these are coated with [[Anti-Corr 113]], a highly penetrating anti-corrosion gel, prompting a visual inspection only.

Having found no trace of contraband, the inspection team reseals the cargo with [[Imperial Customs Bureau seal|Imperial Customs Seals]] and leaves the ship. Falconi reveals his tricks: Harlison’s refined [[Tibanna/Legends|Tibanna gas]] was concealed in the crates at the entrance of the hold that the inspection team overlooked, while the military-grade repulsor coils were hidden in the larger industrial ones that the stormtroopers didn't dare to touch. To top it off, Luies was in on the plan, having swapped Dutan Lee’s weapons cargo before bringing it to the docking bay. Moreover, with the newly applied Imperial Seals, Falconi and his crew can now bypass all future inspections on these crates.

